<Author>Gemsaloola
<Content>Perfect for visiting Amsterdam on a budget I booked ITC Hotel on a whim after my holiday to Prague was cancelled so it all happened very quick. It was only after booking that it occured to me that I should check the reviews - when I did I wave of fear came over me as 90% of the reviews are unfavourable.I'd booked the hotel for myself, my boyfriend and two friends, I warned them that it may not be very good at all as I'd read the horrific reviews on here. But we were pleasantly suprised on our arrival. The hotel is very reasonably priced and travellers need to remember that it is a two star hotel, you can't go and expect five star luxury.The rooms are simple yet comfortable, warm and clean. The staff seemed nice and let us store our baggage at the hotel from 10am until the 2pm check in time which was very helpful.One thing that you may need to be prepared for - they asked us to pay 20 euros on arrival for tax for the four of us, after paying I checked my booking forms which stated that 拢4.99 was included in the price per person per night for tax and services. Had I known this before I would have protested.All in all a nice little hotel, nice views of the canal from the front. I wouldn't recommend this to anyopne other that students and young travellers, if you plan on going out for most of the day and night then its perfect but if you're looking for a romantic break or city retreat this hotel won't be for you.I hope this helps further ITC Hotel users. 
