<Content>What a dump! When I saw the charming building featured in their advert I was looking forward with my friend to staying at this hotel. It is a typical old Dutch town house. But it has been ruined by the owners. It has been cheaply converted with worn blue carpet on the stairs and lots of plyboard. My room although of a decent size had a particularly bad damp smell and the tiny bathroom was too basic to bear. My friend's room was poky in the extreme. The beds were like cheap camp beds. I have stayed in basic hotels before and found them ok; this was VERY depressing. We parked our bags and went out the evening we arrived but every time we thought about going back to the hotel we felt depressed. So we booked into another hotel. I definitely would not recommend this hotel unless you are a student and used to youth hostel-style accommodation. 
