<Author>jmghart62
<Content>Don't write it off Less than 24 hours before my girlfriend and I were due to arrive at the ITC Hotel, I decided to check out the reviews. I then spent the time when I should have been packing hastily trying to find another hotel to stay at because what I read panicked me so much. But, as I struggled to find anywhere in our budget (bearing in mind we would have been forced to pay a cancellation fee to the ITC), we went ahead. All the excitement I had been feeling about a week in Amsterdam had vanished as I dreaded what was waiting for us. I am 44, I am past the point of hostels and roughing it, I like my little luxuries - like a comfortable bathroom, clean sheets and towels - and the reviews here did not fill me with a great deal of hope.Well, I am home again and the first thing I would say is, I'd go back to the ITC tomorrow. OK, perhaps the website is a little misleading... but, remember how much you are paying. Could you get a room in a boutique hotel for around 85 euros a night? I don't think so.The staff were friendly, our rooms was made up every day and we were always given clean towels. Yes, the room needed a lick of paint; yes, the bathroom was very small; yes, it is very basic.But, it is a cheap and cheerful base to explore a great city. If you are looking for something special, then look elsewhere... but if all you need is a bed for the night, go ahead and book. 
