<Content>Its still a dive with no service We have just returned home from staying at ITC Hotel Amsterdam from Thursday 20th to Monday 24th July. I have to say we are generally appalled and disgusted by the hotel standards. We were warned by friends not to use your hotel when they stayed in a basement room in February and they said it was cold, damp, smelly and shabby. Unfortunately we did not take their advice. The room we stayed in room 4 was advertised on their website as a luxury room and we paid 125 euros a night (cash as there was a 5% supplement if we did not). The following are the complaints: 1. The room was badly furnished and in need of refurbishment. 2. The shower was broken. 3. The sink was not en-suite but in the bedroom and did not have a plug 4. The room was NOT cleaned during our stay and one day the maid did not come in at all (Sunday) 5. The carpet and bedding smelled musty and the sheets were old and ill fitting. In all this has to be the worst accommodation I have stayed in since I was a student. The only ever time a hotel was as bad was a gay run hotel in Dublin. It strikes me that as a gay run and advertised establishment that tey are simply ripping off the gay market. Payment is made in cash up front before you get a chance to see the room...no wonder! We were unable to make our complaint at the time as the only person we saw at any time in reception was the maid, who could hardly speak English. We did finally manage to get some clean towels on the Sunday but the room was not touched. 
