<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>disgusting I took my girlfriend to Amsterdam recently, her first trip to continental europe. i decided to look for a gay and lesbian friendly hotel for our stay and was impressed by the itc web site. I really thought the place looked nice. So wrong!!! I have never stayed in such a dive in all my life! The place was filthy. The carpets looked like they had not been hoovered in months. The walls were covered in stains. The corners were thick with cobwebs. The ensuite bathroom in the room was litte more than a toilet and a shower ( that did the hot,cold,hot,cold,hot,cold thing) stuck into a cupboard in the room. Thankfully the bedding and towels seemed to be clean, which is more than can be said for the toilet. The smell of stale urine was most unpleasant. I was amazed to see shoe shiners in the hall outside the bedrooms. To cleans your feet after walking on the carpets perhaps?? We had booked a small double room for 90 euros per night, but were informed on our arrival that we had been given a free upgrade to a large room which should have cost 125 euros per night. I have visited Amsterdam several times before and for the same room rate have had much better accomodation with breakfast included. Not that i would have eaten anything that had been prepared or even stored in this place! I can only imagine what my girlfriend ( an American ) made of the state of the place. Only fatigue made us stay there for the night. My advice to any gay travellers thinking about staying here would be to take your money else where. There is no problem with getting accomodation for same sex couples in Amsterdam and for the money that you would spend to stay in this hovel, you would be much better off in any other hotel. The only reason i have given the itc a rating of 1 is that there is no option available to award it less. I only hope that people do not fall in to tha same trap as i did and believe the very obviously outdated or fabricated photos and descriptions on the itc web site. 
