<Author>ipsque
<Content>Best breakfast I've ever had I had stayed at the ITC Hotel back in 1990 when I got out of college. It was my first time to Europe, and the guys were very kind and considerate, even let us leave our bikes in the hallway.I was very excited to return in 2003. We did not this time have a canal view (thought the tram would be too loud). They were very helpful about letting us store our bags, with finding us a natural food store and storing my partner's special bread - she doesn't eat wheat. I was delighted to see that they had remodeled the common area into a lovely breakfast area, and that you can have breakfast overlooking the canal. Our room was good sized by European standards, and was very comfortable. Breakfast was wonderful (I'll always remember the ham and the great cappuccino machine), and was served later than any other hotel I have stayed at - until noon on weekdays and 1 on weekends. It has a great location, walking distance to anywhere in the centrum. I had always remembered Prinsengracht. I love Amsterdam and the Netherlands, and I hope to stay at the ITC again in the future. 
