<Content>Coming Back to Amsterdam After 3 years, I'm returning to Amsterdam, and looking for a nice BB to stay in. After my miserable experience at the ITC in 2002, I checked to see if things had improved. ( in the 80's and 90's I stayed here several times, and loved the ITC, it's wonderful atmosphere, and location).I see that two years later, according to reviews, they are still renovating the public rooms.I see that people are still as unhappy with the unfriendly new management, as we were surprised and disappointed by them in 2002.The last time we stayed, the breakfast room was torn up; everything about the hotel was worn and threadbare. Breakfast was no longer included, and wasn't served at the times posted. It was dirty, and noisy. When we decided to look elsewhere for the rest of our stay ( we'd booked 5 nights) the manageress threatened us, attempted not to give me back my credit card, then immediately charged for the full 5 nights stay (mastercard eventually denied their claim)Amsterdam is a wonderful place... the ITC, sadly, isn't any longer. Don't stay here. 
