<Author>Two-PS-Mikes
<Content>Dismal and Depressing First, the pluses: a big room with plenty of space, a canal view, free internet access in the lobby, and a good location. Everything else about this hotel, however, was just dismal and depressing. The whole place needs a paint job and the carpet had reached the stage of worn out years ago. Likewise with the towels which made Motel6 quality towels look good! The hallways and stairwells have an institutional feeling to them, like a group home for recovering addicts. Our room was only marginally clean and the housekeeping staff seemed to get around to their duties when the mood struck them (on one day, it was 5 p.m. and the room still had not been cleaned). The design of the bathroom was terrible -- a room with a toilet jammed into it (which had to be ridden side saddle) and another with a shower; the sink was in the bedroom itself. It is clear that the owners just stopped caring about this place a long time ago as evidenced by the cheap Van Gogh print that was mounted crooked in its cheap frame. As other reviewers have noted, the photos on the website must be years old as they do not remotely indicate the true deterioration of the property. And that canal view -- you get too look at a houseboat that looks as though it could sink at any moment (similar houseboats are all too prevalent in Amsterdam). While some of the cheaper rooms in the hotel might prove to be a reasonable tradeoff for those who are on a very strict budget, we feel pretty sure that it is possible to do a lot better for the 125 Euros/night that we paid even in an expensive city like Amsterdam. What a dissapointment! 
